react
react is open source js library used for buildin single page applications

features
virtual dom---- diffing algorithm --- reconciliation
component based architecture
spa 

props
props are read only inputs used to pass the information from 
parent component to child component

component 
reusable part of code used to render part of UI

types of components 
1) functional components
hooks - built in function used to implement the react features

2) class components
life cycle methods



state
state is like a variable used to manage the dynamic nature of a 
component or used to store the daata
react rerenders whenever the state changes

import useState from 'react'
const [statename,setStatename]=useState(intial value)

const [count,setCount]=useState(0)

count---varaible name
setCount---function used to change the state value
useState -
it is a hook in functional component that is used to manage
the state


useEffect
useEffect is a hook that is used to manage side effects
like apicalls, settimeout,setinterval and localstorage

import {useEffect} from 'react'

//it will run whenever the state changes
useEffect(()=>{
    console.log('requestt')
})

//useEffect with empty dependence array
useEffect(()=>{
    console.log('requestt')
},[])

//useEffect with dependece array with state value
useEffect(()=>{
    console.log('requestt')
},[val])